Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
ecoDeleteBacksideConstraint(25.10)          ecoDeleteBacksideConstraint(25.10)

Name
       ecoDeleteBacksideConstraint  - Deletes the backside layer constraint on
       a net

Syntax
       ecoDeleteBacksideConstraint

       [-help]

       -net <netName>

       Deletes the backside layer constraint on a net. The command can  delete
       the  backside  constraint on a net that has only pure FTV cells and all
       terms on the backside. It does not update the routing, and  leaves  the
       routing open. You need to update the routing and re-time to see the ef-
       fect of the change.

       The  command  errors out and does nothing if it is called on a def net,
       routed on the front side.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each ecoDeleteBacksideConstraint.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man ecoDeleteBacksideConstraint

       -net <netName >
              Specifies  the  name  of  the  net  on which FTV cells are to be
              deleted. The net should have some ftv nets defined or should  be
              fully routed on the backside. If called on a frontside only net,
              the command will not work.

